<section class="Sh">
<h1 class="Sh" id="EXAMPLES"><a class="permalink" href="#EXAMPLES">EXAMPLES</a></h1>
<div class="Bd Bd-indent"><code class="Li">fssconfig fss0 /usr
  /tmp/back</code></div>
<div class="Bd Bd-indent"><code class="Li">mount /dev/fss0 /mnt</code></div>
<p class="Pp">Configures the snapshot device <span class="Pa">fss0</span> as a
    snapshot of the <span class="Pa">/usr</span> file system, and makes the
    contents of the snapshot available via <span class="Pa">/mnt</span>. Data
    written through <span class="Pa">/usr</span> will be backed up in
    <span class="Pa">/tmp/back</span>.</p>
<p class="Pp"></p>
<div class="Bd Bd-indent"><code class="Li">fssconfig fss1 / /dev/rsd0e
  8192</code></div>
<p class="Pp">Configures the snapshot device <span class="Pa">fss1</span> as a
    snapshot of the <span class="Pa">/</span> file system. Data written through
    <span class="Pa">/</span> will be backed up in
    <span class="Pa">/dev/rsd0e</span>. The backup will take place in units of
    8192 bytes.</p>
<p class="Pp"></p>
<div class="Bd Bd-indent"><code class="Li">fssconfig -u fss0</code></div>
<p class="Pp">Unconfigures the <span class="Pa">fss0</span> device.</p>
</section>
